    "body": "Yes, that's exactly what I've been experiencing. Using the default Rocket Pool config, which uses a Prometheus pull configuration. All #4519 seems to do is spamming the logs with errors about not setting a PushGateway.\r\n\r\nYou can mute it by explicitly setting `--Metrics.PushGatewayUrl=\"\"`, but requiring that for pull users seems like worse UX, not better.\r\nIs that the intended behavior going forward? Should all pull users have to explicitly set this?",
